# MUST Market Intelligence Agent - Cursor Configuration
# This project follows a strict three-agent architecture

## Project Architecture
This is a multi-agent AI system with three specialized agents:
- agents/watcher.py: ONLY handles Binance data fetching and anomaly flagging
- agents/analyst.py: ONLY handles scoring logic (momentum, volume, liquidity, authenticity)
- agents/narrator.py: ONLY handles LLM prompt construction and plain-English report generation
- core/orchestrator.py: Coordinates agents, never contains business logic
- core/scorer.py: Performance benchmarking only
- core/binance_client.py: Binance API calls only, no analysis logic

## Strict Rules
- NEVER mix agent responsibilities. If modifying watcher.py, do not touch analyst logic
- NEVER hardcode API keys or credentials. Always use os.getenv()
- ALWAYS add sys.path.insert(0, project_root) at top of any new executable file
- NEVER import agents directly in run.py - use Orchestrator only
- ALL Binance API calls go through core/binance_client.py exclusively

## Code Style
- All functions must have docstrings
- All API calls must have try/except error handling
- Use type hints on all function signatures
- Keep each agent file under 300 lines

## When Adding Features
- New data sources: add methods to binance_client.py first
- New analysis metrics: add to analyst.py score_opportunity() only
- New output formats: add to narrator.py format_final_output() only
- New scheduling logic: add to orchestrator.py only

## Testing
- Always test with python run.py --test before python run.py --once
- Mock data is in run.py test mode, do not modify mock values
- Performance scoring is in core/scorer.py